<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Emperor" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Emperor,</orth> title of the sovereigns of Rome: <bibl n="shak. tit 1.184" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 184</bibl> etc. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.7.21" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.6.28" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.90" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 14, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 76</bibl> etc. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.2" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 2</bibl> etc. Hence, of the lords paramount of Germany: <bibl n="shak. jn 1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.42" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 42</bibl>. V Chor. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.42" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 42</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 176</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 176</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.162" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 162</bibl> etc. of the sovereign of Russia: <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 120</bibl>. Uncertain what prince may be meant by it: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 27</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 27</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 27</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.77" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 77</bibl> (the duke of Milan?). Used of the queen-bee: <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.196" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 196</bibl>. Of any supreme degree of human power and splendour: <cit><quote>a present for any e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 72</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 195</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>